    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i hear you on the \"balance\" thing, but it feels like you're still treating the \"free-market\" view as the default \"correct\" baseline and the other side as just a \"specific\" exception. if a policy actually saves thousands of jobs in a vital industry, isn't that an objective win, regardless of what a textbook says about efficiency?",
