      "content": "Protecting jobs in vital domestic industries is a powerful, tangible political and social argument that cannot be dismissed by abstract economic theory. When a policy demonstrably preserves livelihoods and critical supply chains, its immediate benefit to the populace is a real, measurable win. The debate then shifts from pure efficiency to the societal value placed on employment stability versus pure market competition. Ultimately, the \"right\" policy depends on whether a society prioritizes immediate job security or long-term, globally optimized efficiency.",
